videos.headline: Kiel scores rushing TD for Cincinnati
videos.description: Gunner Kiel made things happen with his legs for Cincinnati, diving and stretching for the pylon to give the Bearcats a 7-0 lead over Memphis less than two minutes into the game on ESPN.

videos.headline: A. Gantz 35 yd FG GOOD
videos.description: Andrew Gantz 35 yd FG GOOD

videos.headline: Memphis surges ahead with long TD
videos.description: Paxton Lynch connects with Anthony Miller on an 82-yard TD to give Memphis a 14-10 lead over Cincinnati in the first quarter on ESPN.

videos.headline: Bearcats QB leaves game after hit to the head
videos.description: Cincinnati Bearcats QB Gunner Kiel gets hit on a 3-yard scramble on a shoulder-to-helmet collision. He is in the locker room and under medical evaluation, but he is awake and moving all four limbs.

videos.headline: A. Gantz 27 yd FG BLOCKED,blocked by TEAM
videos.description: Andrew Gantz 27 yd FG BLOCKED blocked by TEAM

videos.headline: Cincinnati grabs lead with long TD
videos.description: Hayden Moore, who replaced the injured Gunner Kiel at QB, hit Chris Moore for a 68-yard TD to give Cincinnati a 17-14 lead over Memphis early in the second quarter on ESPN.

videos.headline: Gunner Kiel awake, moving all limbs
videos.description: Kaylee Hartung updates the condition of Cincinnati QB Gunner Kiel, who was taken off the field in a stretcher in the first quarter of the game vs. Memphis.

videos.description: Memphis CB Reggie Ball pins Hayden Moore's pass against his headgear for the interception.

videos.headline: Tigers kicker makes a 40-yard FG
videos.description: Memphis Tigers K Jake Elliott makes a 40-yard FG and gives his team the lead in the third quarter against Cincinnati.

videos.headline: Moore to Morrison for 18-yard pass
videos.description: Bearcats QB Hayden Moore completes a pass to WR Max Morrison for an 18-yard gain for a first down against the Tigers.

videos.headline: Bearcats take the lead with a 36-yard FG
videos.description: Bearcats K Andrew Gantz makes his 4th FG of the game with a boot from 36. Cincinnati lead 33-31 with 1:27 remaining in the third quarter against the Tigers.

videos.headline: Tigers take lead in 4th quarter
videos.description: Paxton Lynch went play-action and found Alan Cross, who raced into the end zone for the TD. Memphis has a 38-33 lead early in the 4th quarter on ESPN/WatchESPN.

videos.description: Hayden Moore found Max Morrison for 6 on the 10th lead change of the game, but the two-point conversion was no good. Cincinnati has a 39-38 lead over Memphis early in the 4th quarter on ESPN/WatchESPN.
